						               													<description>Manos a la olla is a game for 2 to 4 players. Win the final of this magic potion contest before the other witches - cheats and curses welcome!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each witch will take a magic recipe to prepare. During each turn, each witch plays an action card from her hand to collect new ingredients or take them from the cupboard. You can also use teleport spells to move ingredients (or steal them, ha ha!) between the witches' cauldrons. Finally, you can use a transmute action to magically swap one ingredient for another. As witches are not immune to attacks and traps, the Witch's Reflexes card will save you from more than one trouble!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Witches also get fed up with being cheated, so they can sometimes use spells that will stun their opponents - watch out for them! Among the 20 ingredients, some are very rare. So you'll have to fight for them with other witches to complete your recipe.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Only when your cauldron contains the exact ingredients for your recipe will you be victorious - remember, you must make two to get it! The rules of Hands in the Pot are extremely simple to allow the witch players to interact with each other as much as possible.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
